

.text: Indicates the start of the code section.

.global or .globl: Declares a symbol (such as a function or variable) as global, making it visible to other modules or files.

.equ: Defines a constant or assigns a value to a symbol.


.include: Includes the contents of another file in the assembly code.

.data: Marks the beginning of a data section where initialized data is defined.
.bss: Marks the beginning of a section containing uninitialized data.

.word: Reserves space for one or more 32-bit words in the data section.
.byte: Reserves space for one or more bytes.
.space: Reserves a specified amount of space (in bytes) in data or bss section.
